================================================================
CONTEXTLENS — DASHBOARD NOT SHOWING PROJECTS FIX
================================================================

ROOT CAUSE
----------
Backend writes all data to:
  users/contextlens-demo-user/projects/...

Dashboard reads from:
  users/{auth.currentUser.uid}/projects/...

These two UIDs do not match so dashboard shows nothing.
Your data IS in Firestore — it just needs to be read correctly.

Your 3 projects (Portfolio + 2 others) are already there.
They will show up the moment you apply these fixes.

================================================================
FIX 1 — FIRESTORE SECURITY RULES (DO THIS FIRST — 2 MINUTES)
================================================================

Go to:
  Firebase Console
  → Your Project
  → Firestore Database
  → Rules tab

REPLACE everything with this:

----------------------------------------------------------------
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if true;
    }
  }
}
----------------------------------------------------------------

Click PUBLISH.

This removes the read block immediately.
Without this, even correct UID reads will fail silently.

================================================================
FIX 2 — DASHBOARD HOOKS (READ FROM CORRECT UID)
================================================================

The dashboard needs to fall back to 'contextlens-demo-user'
when no auth session exists — because that is where your
backend is writing data right now.

----------------------------------------------------------------
FIND these files in your dashboard src/ folder:

  - useProjects.ts  (or wherever projects are fetched)
  - useEpisodes.ts  (or wherever episodes are fetched)
  - useCalls.ts     (or wherever calls are fetched)
  - api.ts          (if you have a central data fetcher)
----------------------------------------------------------------

IN EVERY FILE that reads from Firestore, find this pattern:

  BEFORE (wrong):
  ---------------
  const uid = auth.currentUser?.uid;
  const ref = collection(db, 'users', uid, 'projects');

  AFTER (correct):
  ----------------
  const uid = auth.currentUser?.uid || 'contextlens-demo-user';
  const ref = collection(db, 'users', uid, 'projects');

Do the same for episodes:

  BEFORE:
  const ref = collection(db, 'users', auth.currentUser?.uid, 'episodes');

  AFTER:
  const uid = auth.currentUser?.uid || 'contextlens-demo-user';
  const ref = collection(db, 'users', uid, 'episodes');

Do the same for calls:

  BEFORE:
  const ref = collection(db, 'users', auth.currentUser?.uid, 'calls');

  AFTER:
  const uid = auth.currentUser?.uid || 'contextlens-demo-user';
  const ref = collection(db, 'users', uid, 'calls');

----------------------------------------------------------------
IF you have a central uid getter — update it in ONE place:
----------------------------------------------------------------

  FIND in src/hooks/useAuth.ts or src/lib/firebase.ts:

    export function getCurrentUid(): string | null {
      return auth.currentUser?.uid || null;
    }

  REPLACE with:

    export function getCurrentUid(): string {
      return auth.currentUser?.uid || 'contextlens-demo-user';
    }

  Now every hook that calls getCurrentUid() will automatically
  fall back to the demo user. No other changes needed.

